<div class="container"><section class="py-5"><h1 class="font-weight-bolder text-center text-capitalize text-dark font-family-san-serif font-size-3pt5rem px-3">Priority Service</h1></section><section class="py-3 case-study-left-padding pull-left"><div class="col-12 col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12 col-xl-12 pull-left" style="float: inherit;"><p>Symbio Energy is committed to providing you&nbsp;the&nbsp;best customer service&nbsp;possible. We understand that some of our customers have special needs. Priority services is our way of showing that we are there for these customers and that we care.</p><h5>Who Can Apply?</h5><p>You can be put on our priority services register if you are one or more of the below:</p><ul><li>are of pensionable age</li><li>are disabled or chronically sick</li><li>have a long-term medical condition</li><li>have a hearing or visual impairment or additional communication needs</li><li>are in a&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ofgem.gov.uk/consumers/household-gas-and-electricity-guide/extra-help-energy-services/priority-services-register-people-need" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">vulnerable situation</a></li></ul><h5>Our Priority Services Include:</h5><ul><li>Free quarterly visits to read your electricity meter</li><li>Your electricity bill in large print</li><li>A password scheme, to identify Symbio Energy Personnel, when they visit you</li><li>Arrange for communications to be sent to a friend or carer, nominated by you</li></ul><p>If there are any other special requests you would like us to provide, please do let us know. We will do our best to accommodate your request.</p><h5>How To Sign Up To The Priority Services Register</h5><p>If you think you need to be on the register, or you want to apply on behalf of someone, please do make contact.</p></div></section></div>

